				<li id="16636779" class="cmnt-root" data="3" data-d="1650429593000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579140/Ancestral-Spirit's-Horn" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 Apr 2022 00:39</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16636779" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Doing a mix of a caster and a melee build. This talisman was pretty useful for a while, but it does start to lose usefulness in later levels as your magic bar gets bigger and you get access to stronger and more expensive spells. For spells that don&apos;t cost much FP like Carian Slicer, this is great, but for beefier spells, you&apos;d be better off just chugging a flask. <br/><br/>Definitely don&apos;t sleep on this like some comments suggest, but if you&apos;re heavy into the caster side of things, you&apos;d probably be better off looking for talismans that improve the power of your spells or how many slots you have. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16636779" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16636779" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></sp